Every study proves remote workers are more productive, so why are we still pretending offices are necessary? I just put in less effort on the in-office days. If I'm commuting 45 minutes twice a day, that is 90 minutes of work fewer they will get out of me. On WFH days I'll work until 7:30 PM. In the office, it is so loud. People are just on their calls, not "collaborating" in person. I have to spend 30 minutes setting up and 30 minutes breaking down each day due to open desk shared seating. The thought of me having to put noise-canceling headphones on just to focus makes no sense. RTO mandates are not making companies more valuable or productive.
